(5) The Alabama Department of Environmental Management.
85 (6) The Department of Finance.
86 (7) The Department of Insurance.
87 (8) The Alabama Department of Public Health.
88 (9) The State Department of Transportation.
89 (10) The Alabama Emergency Management Agency.
90 (11) The State Forestry Commission.
91 (12) The State Military Department.
92 (13) The Alabama Office of Information Technology.
93 (14) The Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency.
94 (15) The Alabama Public Service Commission
95 (c) The following nonvoting members of the council
96 shall be appointed by the Governor:
97 (1) One member representing property and casualty
98 insurance companies regulated by the Department of Insurance.
99 (2) One member representing entities in the business of
100 emergency management and disaster response.
101 (3) One member representing local government with
102 knowledge and expertise in risk and resilience.
103 (4) One member representing general business entities
104 with knowledge and expertise in risk and resilience.
105 (5) One member representing manufacturing entities with
106 knowledge and expertise in risk and resilience.
107 (6) One member representing independent insurance
108 agents licensed by the Department of Insurance.
109 (7) One member representing an academic research entity
110 based at a public university in this state that focuses on
111 risk and resilience.
112 (8) One member representing small business with
